      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate VAD operating envelope including blood analog viscosity, temperature range, and pulsatile flow waveforms at clinical operating points.",
      "rationale": "Experiments used steady-flow water-glycerol analog at room temperature. Pulsatile flow and physiological temperature effects were not replicated. Blood analog viscosity matched only at 37 degrees C nominal. Significant gap versus VAD clinical conditions."
