      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis index QOI must be directly traceable to the clinical acceptance threshold and must be the primary output driving the device submission decision.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is the primary QOI and is traced to clinical threshold. However, sub-lethal hemolysis markers and platelet activation indices relevant to Class III VAD use are not included as secondary QOIs. Partial traceability only."
